name: Actor
description: anyone who interacts with the system. Authors have to be logged in to modify a model.

name: Command
description: a transactional executor over the model interpreted by the parser.

name: Context
description: a grouping entity defining language boundary.

name: Cube
description: a special domain entity with olap functionalities.

name: Data Service
description: a set of functionalities correlated to a specific Data Type.

name: Domain Entity
description: a set of properties with identity representing something in the actor domain.

name: Domain Repository
description: a storage for domain entities with CRUD functionalities.

name: Domain Service
description: a set of functionalities correlated to a specific Domain Entity.

name: Driver
description: a set of coordinates for a data source reader, writer.

name: EventLog
description: a special domain entity with event sourcing functionalities.

name: Expert
description: a web citizen exposing and consuming system APIs, enriching the system functionalities.

name: Instance
description: a KPrime running instance.

name: Model
description: a potential ubiquitous language specification.

name: Parser
description: a command interpreter and executor.

name: Project
description: a file representation of a context.

name: Source
description: a representation of a data storage container.

name: Story
description: a text file about an interesting aspect of the model.

name: Template
description: a text file containing a story skeleton, ready to be reused.

name: Term
description: a string representing a domain entity or relation of the model.

name: Todo
description: is a potential goal, or task important for the model behaviour.

name: Trace
description: is a folder path with versioning.

name: Transformer
description: is a specification for data schema reversible evolution, an atomic composition or decomposition action.

name: User
description: is an actor with log-in to the system capability.

name: Vocabulary
description: a representation of an ontology used to define term types in the model.

name: map1
description: My mapping they say. Anyway.
